subSubSection.paragraph:
Coloration
(
Figs. 104–107
). The base color of pedipalps, chelicerae, legs, sternites and metasomal segments I–III and V is uniformly yellow to yellowish brown. The pedipalp chela in males can be almost white. Metasomal segment IV is dark brown to black, telson yellowish brown to orange. Carapace and tergites can be yellow (male 
holotype
) or brown to black (female 
paratypes
)

